HEADWORD: Amnigenous
<hw>Am*nig"e*nous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>amnigena</ets>; <ets>amnis</ets> a river + root <ets>gen</ets> of
<ets>gignere</ets> to beget.]</ety> <def>Born or bred in, of, or near a
river.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

